From: Avery Felts <averyfelts@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 18:30:37 -0600
Subject: [PATCH 15/15] ntdll: accept relocated initial process images

A successfully mapped initial executable may return a nonzero NT success
status such as STATUS_IMAGE_NOT_AT_BASE. Do not route those images through
start.exe; reserve that fallback for actual NT failures. This prevents an
ASLR-dependent prefix bootstrap from discarding a valid relocated wineboot.exe
and subsequently failing to load kernel32.dll.

This patch is distributed under Wine's LGPL-2.1-or-later terms.
---
 dlls/ntdll/unix/env.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/dlls/ntdll/unix/env.c b/dlls/ntdll/unix/env.c
index bdd3e51a66..bb33deb4cf 100644
--- a/dlls/ntdll/unix/env.c
+++ b/dlls/ntdll/unix/env.c
@@ -1950,7 +1950,7 @@ static RTL_USER_PROCESS_PARAMETERS *build_initial_params( void **module )
         }
     }
 
-    if (status)  /* try launching it through start.exe */
+    if (!NT_SUCCESS(status))  /* try launching it through start.exe */
     {
         static const char *args[] = { "start.exe", "/exec" };
         free( nt_name.Buffer );
